  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'd go the template way as well. If we start doing special code for Bootstrap we're going into a maintenance nightmare. There will be several Bootstrap version out, and why not also support Foundation, and so on. But more importantly, Bootstrap also requires you to add some specific wrapping divs which will be more complex to handle than simply css classes.\n\nSo definitely, let's keep this css framework agnostic. If we really have a demand for Bootstrap styling, we'll just define and share bootstrap-aware templates.\n",
